#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
kb-search — Hybrid semantic + BM25 search over your Obsidian/kb vault

Combines two search strategies and merges their scores:
  1. BM25 (keyword)   — fast, exact-match, always available
  2. Semantic (vector) — concept-level, finds articles without exact keywords

Semantic embedding sources (tried in order):
  A. llama-server /v1/embeddings  — Gemma 4 neural embeddings (best quality)
                                    Available when llama-server is running.
                                    Enable with: llama-server ... --embeddings
  B. TF-IDF + SVD (numpy LSA)    — offline fallback, no model needed,
                                    genuine semantic search via latent topics

Usage:
    kb-search "who funds youth justice"         → hybrid results
    kb-search "CORENA revolving fund" --bm25    → BM25 only
    kb-search "foundation grants" --semantic    → semantic only
    kb-search "indigenous corps" --excerpt -v   → with highlights
    kb-search --reindex                         → rebuild full index
    kb-search --reindex --embed                 → rebuild + recompute embeddings
    kb-search --stats                           → index statistics

Used by kb query:
    kb-search "<question>" --json --top=15
"""

